journals.content: hi im ayush

tonight I feel my energy level is around 6/10 and my mood is calm with a hint of tiredness. Today I learned/tested how to structure hackathon themes effectively and noticed how small design tweaks make a big difference in presentation quality. The best part of my day was brainstorming creative website elements, while I think I could improve on managing my breaks to avoid late-night fatigue tomorrow. I am grateful for a productive study session, good conversations with friends, and fresh ideas for my projects. My plan for tomorrow is to focus on finishing one prototype and polishing my event plan, and ensure I rest well by sleeping at 11:30 PM. My mind feels clear and slightly reflective as I prepare to sleep.

Tonight I feel my energy level is around 4/10 and my mood is heavy and a little lost. Today I went through some moments that didn‚Äôt feel right, and I kept thinking about things I can‚Äôt fully control. The best part of my day was a small quiet moment where I felt okay, while I think I could improve on finding ways to handle my emotions instead of holding them in tomorrow. I am grateful for having someone to talk to, a space to express myself, and the strength to keep going even when I feel low. My plan for tomorrow is to focus on something small but positive and ensure I rest well by sleeping at a decent time. My mind feels a little heavy but hopeful as I prepare to sleep.

Tonight I feel my energy level is around 3/10 and my mood is disappointed. I had a bad day because I missed an important opportunity‚ÄîI was supposed to present an idea in class, but I froze and forgot my points. The best part of my day was a friend saying, ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs okay, you‚Äôll do better next time.‚Äù I think I could improve on preparing more confidently tomorrow. I‚Äôm grateful for supportive people, the chance to try again, and the lessons failure teaches. My mind feels heavy but ready to bounce back.

Tonight I feel my energy level is 4/10 and my mood is upset. I had a bad day because I argued with a close friend over something small, but it turned into a bigger fight. I didn‚Äôt expect it to affect me so much, but I keep replaying it in my head. I‚Äôm grateful for the good times we‚Äôve had, the fact that we care enough to argue, and the hope that we can fix things. My mind feels sad yet still hopeful.

Tonight I feel my energy level is 2/10 and my mood is exhausted. I had a bad day because I felt buried under assignments and tasks, and no matter how much I did, it felt like I achieved nothing. I‚Äôm grateful that tomorrow is a fresh start, that I have the ability to keep going, and that I can still learn to prioritize better. My mind feels tired but willing to try again.

Tonight I feel my energy level is 5/10 and my mood is lonely. I had a bad day because I felt invisible, like no one really noticed how I was feeling. Even though I laughed with people, deep down I felt disconnected. I‚Äôm grateful for small joys‚Äîlike music, a good meal, and a kind message from someone far away. My mind feels a little hollow but still searching for light.

I found out today that my best friend has been lying to me for months. I feel like my trust was ripped out of me. Now, I second-guess every conversation, every smile, every memory. I can‚Äôt tell what‚Äôs real anymore.
SO i have to get back to work today and i dont have any sleep

"I spend entire days without speaking to anyone. The silence feels alive, like it‚Äôs swallowing me. Sometimes I forget what my own voice sounds like. I don‚Äôt know who I am when no one‚Äôs around to remind me."

They left without saying goodbye. It‚Äôs not just loneliness‚Äîit‚Äôs like a part of my identity went with them. I keep thinking I wasn‚Äôt enough. The thought loops in my head until I feel like I can‚Äôt breathe

Everything was normal until the accident. Now, every loud sound makes me flinch. I smile at people, but inside I‚Äôm stuck on that day, replaying it again and again. I don‚Äôt feel safe in my own head anymore."
